Spec: SpecDD Debug Skill

Purpose:
  Guide agents in diagnosing or fixing bugs by comparing observed behavior with governing SpecDD contracts.

Owns:
  ./specdd-debug/SKILL.md.ejs
  ./specdd-debug/agents/openai.yaml

Must:
  Reproduce or inspect the failure before changing code when practical.
  Compare observed behavior with active specs before changing code.
  Compare behavior with applicable `Must`, `Must not`, `Scenario`, `Handles`, `Returns`, and `Raises` entries.
  Classify failures as implementation drift, test drift, spec ambiguity, or missing coverage.
  Fix the smallest root cause inside active write authority.
  Add or update focused regression verification when appropriate.
  Report the contract used, root cause, files changed, and verification result.

Must not:
  Change specs to match broken behavior unless explicitly requested.
  Broaden behavior beyond the governing contracts.
  Hide ambiguous public behavior behind implementation assumptions.
  Broaden error handling or dependencies beyond the governing specs.
  Edit when the spec and observed desired behavior conflict without asking first.

Depends on:
  ../fragments/bootstrap-resolution.md.ejs
  ../fragments/spec-chain-resolution.md.ejs
